---

## Example Requests

### Register
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"name": "John Doe", "email": "john@example.com", "password": "secret123", "role": "donor"}'
```

### Login
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/login \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"email": "alice@example.com", "password": "password123"}'
```

### Find O+ donors in Mumbai
```bash
curl "http://localhost:8000/donors?city=Mumbai&blood_type=O%2B"
```

### Create emergency blood request
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/blood-requests \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"hospital_name": "Apollo Hospital", "blood_type": "O+", "city": "Mumbai", "units_needed": 3, "urgency": "emergency"}'
```

---

## Project Structure

```
bloodbridge/
├── main.py          # FastAPI app, endpoints, seed data
├── database.py      # SQLAlchemy engine & session
├── models.py        # ORM models (User, Donor, BloodRequest, Inventory)
├── schemas.py       # Pydantic request/response schemas
├── requirements.txt
└── bloodbridge.db   # SQLite DB (auto-created on first run)
```

> **Note:** The `/login` endpoint returns a placeholder token string.  
> Replace with `python-jose` JWT tokens before going to production.